    - ["mp3196024",  operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy.__dict__,  "__rshift__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __pow__, __lshift__, __rshift__ across all 8 multiprocessing subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 8 classes x 3 methods = 24 rows.
# __pow__:    false for all 8 — exponentiation is not defined for any mp type.
# __lshift__: false for all 8 — left-shift is not defined for any mp type.
# __rshift__: false for all 8 — right-shift is not defined for any mp type.
# All 24 values are false.
# multiprocessing is a process-based synchronous concurrency library.
#   Its API surface is entirely method-based: process lifecycle, pool dispatch,
#   result retrieval, and IPC proxy method forwarding. No arithmetic or bitwise
#   operator overloading appears anywhere in the type hierarchy.
# Proxy type note: BaseListProxy, _BaseDictProxy, _BaseSetProxy mirror the
#   method interface of list, dict, and set respectively — but they do so
#   via named methods proxied over IPC, not via Python operator overloads.
#   The underlying types (list, dict, set) themselves return false for all
#   three operators: list has no **/__lshift__/__rshift__; dict has no
#   **/__lshift__/__rshift__; set has no **/__lshift__/__rshift__.
#   The proxy types therefore also return false, consistently with their
#   underlying types.
# pool.AsyncResult note: the "Async" in the name refers to non-blocking result
#   retrieval (the result is fetched later via get()), not to asyncio or Python
#   async/await. AsyncResult does not define any arithmetic or bitwise dunders.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

